{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/why-should-you-use-kotlin-for-machine-learning-on-android-6dbab8ac59da", "time": 1683009510.793877, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/why-should-you-use-kotlin-for-machine-learning-on-android-6dbab8ac59da/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How Could Kotlin Be The New \u201cPython\u201d For ML On Android? | by Shubham Panchal | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How Could Kotlin Be The New \u201cPython\u201d For ML On Android?", "description": "Machine Learning | Python | Kotlin | Android | TensorFlow | ML | AI"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://numpy.org/", "anchor_text": "NumPy", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://pandas.pydata.org/", "anchor_text": "Pandas", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://scikit-learn.org/", "anchor_text": "scikit-learn", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://kotlinlang.org/api/latest/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.collections/", "anchor_text": "doc", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://developer.android.com/kotlin/coroutines", "anchor_text": "Kotlin Coroutines", "paragraph_index": 12}], "all_paragraphs": ["Developing ML algorithms will sound thrilling if you\u2019re a programming enthusiast. First things, first. Imagine you are about to create a Decision Tree Classifier in Python. Why would do you? Most probably you\u2019ll use NumPy for array manipulations and Pandas for processing data. Some might use scikit-learn\u2019s DecisionTreeClassifier. If you are about to create a decision tree from scratch, you can easily do this using Python.", "Like other programming languages, in Python, you don\u2019t need to explicitly specify a variable\u2019s data type. Also, it has numerous packages available via pip so save our lives! But as the number of edge devices around us increases, you probably have to code ML algorithms on platforms like iOS, Android, Rasberry Pi. Talking about Android ( as I am an Android Developer, which you may have inferred from the story\u2019s title ), working with arrays could be a nightmare on Java (also remember those semicolons!).", "Enter Kotlin. A new programming language for Android. It has easy to use methods for array manipulations which makes it powerful and developer-friendly. Its syntax resembles Python too. In this story, we learn about some excellent Kotlin functions which will help you in your ML journey through Android.", "If you want to perform image classification or detection on some of your user\u2019s photos, we can use Kotlin\u2019s map function.", "In Java, you probably have to write a for loop iterating through the files and converting them to Bitmap one by one.", "In particular, the map() function in Kotlin is very useful for performing different operations on an array.", "Computing min, max, an average of numbers stored in an array is important for various ML algorithms. Be it the argmax function or max and min functions in Python, we can have them all in Kotlin!", "In the snippet above, I have used the map function within the map function to normalize a multi dimensional array.", "See how we can successively use map to perform any operation on an array. There are more methods like groupBy and binarySearch which might be useful. See this doc.", "For instance, in a decision tree algorithm, you need the probability of a certain element in an array, for calculating information gain. Likewise, for TF-IDF, we need to calculate term frequencies and IDFs too. With Kotlin\u2019s count and filter methods it\u2019s easier to work with probabilities and frequencies of various elements in an array.", "Filtering is also useful when you are preprocessing data for an NLP model. Several tasks like tokenization, removing stop words, and punctuation could be performed using the filterfunction.", "An example with which you can create a ( word , frequency ) vocabulary and store it as a HashMap<String,Int> ,", "Kotlin Coroutines can help us run ML models on background threads thus delivering premium user experience. If you\u2019re using a model to enhance the resolution of an image ( super-resolution ), you\u2019ll like to run it asynchronously. Learn more about using Kotlin Coroutines here,", "We all love Decision Trees right? You can code them in Kotlin as well,", "They are simple, right? We need something challenging! What about Feedforward Neural Networks ( with backpropagation )?", "Reinforcement learning, Q learning? We also serve that!", "An end-to-end FaceNet implementation on Android ( with 100% Kotlin ),", "As a keen ML + Android developer, I have constantly build ML algorithms right from scratch in Kotlin.", "So, how\u2019s Kotlin for machine learning? I hope you\u2019ll find it better than Java! If you have more examples where you have used Kotlin for some ML algorithm make sure you mention it in the comments, to get it mentioned here! Thanks for reading!.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "\ud83d\ude07 Loves Android and ML, \ud83d\udca1 answering your thought-provoking questions in ML intuitively, \ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83c\udf93 aspiring ML researcher"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F6dbab8ac59da&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwhy-should-you-use-kotlin-for-machine-learning-on-android-6dbab8ac59da&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwhy-should-you-use-kotlin-for-machine-learning-on-android-6dbab8ac59da&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?sourc